Title (Defect)
Missing Pod Ephemeral Storage Limit Caused Node Resource Exhaustion and Pod Evictions
Alternative (shorter):
Pod Without Disk Limit Led to Node Resource Pressure and Evictions
Description
Issue Summary
It was identified that the pod was not configured with an ephemeral storage (disk) limit.
During testing, a single pod continuously consumed disk space, which resulted in node-level resource pressure.
Impact
Excessive disk usage by one pod caused the node to enter a resource low state
Kubernetes triggered pod evictions on the affected node
Other healthy pods on the same node were impacted, even though they were not the source of the issue
Root Cause
The pod specification did not define ephemeral-storage limits
Without disk constraints, the test workload was able to consume node disk resources unchecked
Node-level disk pressure led to eviction decisions by kubelet
Expected Behavior
Pods should have appropriate ephemeral storage requests and limits configured
Excessive disk usage should be contained within the pod itself, without impacting the entire node
Proposed Fix / Recommendation
Define ephemeral-storage requests and limits for all pods
Add validation or policy (e.g. admission controller / policy check) to prevent pods without disk limits from being deployed
Update testing guidelines to avoid running unbounded disk consumption workloads on shared nodes
